{
  "stem": "9995.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So they said probably that we were making-- I think somebody told me that they were saying that we were joking about this guy's head.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I went, and I knew that he was making the list of people to get them out from that transport.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So I came to him, and I went on my knees, and I cried.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And he said, too late.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The list went out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Luckily, my husband has a cousin by exactly the same name, much older, who was in charge of the furrier department, and he was very well liked by the Germans, and he managed to get my husband out.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "When I saw him, we looked like a sight, because one guy, by the name of Colonel [INAUDIBLE], or [INAUDIBLE], incidentally, he was hanged after the war, when he came to Krakow.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Beat him up so one half of his face was completely black.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I was, of course, smashed completely.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I recovered, and I knew that [INAUDIBLE] will not hit me anymore, because otherwise the German would be on his case.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So I told him, when I meet you after the war, in case I survive and you survive, you're not going to live much longer.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And he survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But that was another story, that, after the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Max was working also for-- was a messenger boy for a German who was in charge of all those factories which were in Krakow still, and he liked him very much.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was supposed to be a very big transport because the Russians were approaching Krakow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was already 1944, and Max asked whether I could also stay.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the guy-- he asked about my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he said, you also want your mother-in-law?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My-- I said, I'm going, of course, with my mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
